    "Body": "Remote Woman Remote jobs at trusted companies Close Search for: Search Remote Jobs Marketing Design Developer Product Sales Support Success Stories Community Podcast Post Jobs Menu Public Relations Manager Full Time Anywhere Posted 2 months ago This position has been filled Auth0 Overview Auth0 is a pre-IPO unicorn. We are growing rapidly and looking for exceptional new team members to add to our teams and will help take us to the next level. One team, one score. We never compromise on identity. You should never compromise yours either. We want you to bring your whole self to Auth0. If you\u2019re passionate, practice radical transparency to build trust and respect, and thrive when you\u2019re collaborating, experimenting and learning \u2013 this may be your ideal work environment. We are looking for team members that want to help us build upon what we have accomplished so far and make it better every day. N+1 > N. We are seeking a Public Relations Manager in Southern Europe to support the Global Communications team and continue to drive awareness of Auth0 specifically in France, Spain, Portugal, and Italy. The right candidate will be a French-speaking self-starter who will drive media and analyst relations, thought leadership initiatives, speaking/awards opportunities, and manage our external agency relationship. This role can be based remotely from a home office in France; proximity to Paris is preferred. What You Will Do Support overall Auth0 communications strategy in Southern Europe (primarily France) and serve as key player on team to execute plan Report to our Director, Global Communications and work closely with our PR Manager, EMEA to assist other European markets where necessary Lead the selection of a France-based PR agency to join our EMEA network of agencies in London, Munich, Amsterdam/Brussels Develop a strategic vision and story angles to drive results in Southern Europe with a focus on raising the business profile of Auth0 in new and emerging markets Liaise with the PR agency and internally manage requests for editorial, speaking, analyst, and content opportunities Support agency\u2019s pitching efforts to secure coverage across all forms of earned media including broadcast, print, and online, in national and local media outlets Work closely with other teams in marketing (demand generation, events, ABM, content, product marketing) to align strategies for greater impact Work closely with regional spokespeople to raise their visibility as arbiters of Auth0\u2019s messages Maintain a keen understanding of market-moving news and key industry trends to identify executive thought leadership opportunities Write press releases, bylined articles, speaking abstracts, and product/trend pitches; and serve as editor for all content coming through PR agency Provide support with customer correspondence for press releases and case studies Research and submit relevant CFPs to promote thought leadership of our executive team Assist with event coordination and planning; attend industry events and interface with key media/analysts/influencers What You Bring 5+ years of PR/corporate communications experience, either in-house or in an agency setting Bachelor\u2019s degree or equivalent experience preferred Experience working in B2B technology Outstanding writing and verbal communication skills Fluency in both English and French language skills required An agile team player with ability to thrive in a fast-paced startup environment where direction and goals can evolve quickly to meet goals Fast-learner who is eager to learn and has a discerning eye for detail Strategic thinking, as well as strong execution skills Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and stay highly organized Great interpersonal skills and the ability to engage with many internal/external groups Experience working with the Spanish, Portuguese, and Italian markets is a bonus Ability to travel up to 10% Auth0\u2019s mission is to help developers innovate faster. Every company is becoming a software company and developers are at the center of this shift. They need better tools and building blocks so they can stay focused on innovating. One of these building blocks is identity: authentication and authorization. That\u2019s what we do. Our platform handles 2.5B logins per month for thousands of customers around the world. From indie makers to Fortune 500 companies, we can handle any use case. We like to think that we are helping make the internet safer. We have raised $210M to date and are growing quickly. Our team is spread across more than 35 countries and we are proud to continually be recognized as a great place to work. Culture is critical to us, and we are transparent about our vision and principles. Join us on this journey to make developers more productive while making the internet safer! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Writer/Editor Swingleft We can beat Trump and the GOP, if we get started now. Enter your zip code and find things to do now to help Democrats win the 2020 elections. Anywhere Full Time Posted 3 weeks ago Sr. Product Manager \u2013 Consul Cloud CALIFORNIA \u2013 REMOTE (US) Hashicorp HashiCorp delivers consistent workflows to provision, secure, connect, and run any infrastructure for any application. Anywhere Full Time Posted 1 month ago Technical Account Manager WordPress VIP We help enterprises realize the power of the open web. Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 weeks ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top compan